  "method": [
    "Add the tomatoes, salsa, beans, rice, corn, taco seasoning, cumin, salt, chipotles, and broth to a slow cooker. Stir and cover. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high for 3 to 4 hours.",
    "Add the lentils for the last 40 minutes of cooking. Continue cooking until the lentils are tender. The rice will be tender and most of the liquid will be absorbed. This is the filling.",
    "Lay out the tortillas and place about ⅓ to ½ cup (for a very large burrito) of the filling on each tortilla. Spread the filling down through the center of the tortilla. Fold each end about 1½ inches over the point edge of the beans. Then roll up the tortilla along the long edge. If you have a certain technique that you want to use on these, go right ahead.",
    "Stack up and serve with more salsa, avocado or guacamole, and black olives."
  ],
